# Financial Risk Solvency Resilience Adjustment Amount

## identifier
de5123

## type
float

## definition
Report the value of the adjustment to resilience reserve recognising the potential release of resilience reserves from other statutory funds in accordance with the solvency standard.

The Resilience Reserve is determined as the additional amount that needs to be held before the happening of a prescribed set of changes in the economic environment, such that after the changes the admissible assets of the reporting party are able to meet the policy owner and other liabilities of the statutory fund.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.Solvency.ResilienceAdjustment.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.05
- period=instant
